results.title: Tasting Early Success, Only to Walk Away
results.abstract: Ilya Gurevich and Tal Shaked won the World Junior Chess Championships in the 1990s, but neither of them pursued chess careers as adults.

results.abstract: A gunman killed three people and wounded 16 others before killing himself at Fort Hood, the same sprawling Army base in Texas where in 2009 an officer went on a shooting rampage that left 13 people dead.

results.title: At Times
Archbishop Says He Plans to Sell $2 Million Home
results.abstract: A group of Catholics in the archdiocese in Atlanta had asked that Archbishop Wilton D. Gregory sell the more than 6,000-square-foot home in keeping with the tone of austerity set by Pope Francis.

results.title: Ethics Chief in Georgia Wins Suit Over Ouster
results.abstract: Jurors have awarded the former director of Georgia’s ethics commission $700,000 after ruling in her favor in a lawsuit in which she said her salary had been cut and a deputy removed for investigating complaints against Gov. Nathan Deal.

results.title: Blast Near Falluja Kills 17 Iraq Troops
results.abstract: The soldiers, part of an army convoy patrolling Albu Hadeed, near Falluja, were attacked by gunmen from the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria militant group, security officials said.
